### 5.2 Rydberg Sensor Physics Detail

**Energy Level Diagram:**

```
                    RYDBERG STATE LADDER (Rb-85)
                    
    Energy ▲
           │
    (n+1)P ├─────────────●──────────  ~48 GHz coupling
           │            /│\
           │           / │ \
           │      RF  /  │  \  RF
           │    ─────/   │   \─────
           │              │
      nD   ├─────────────●──────────  Rydberg state (n~50-70)
           │             ▲
           │             │ 480 nm (Coupling laser)
           │             │
     5P₃/₂ ├─────────────●──────────  Intermediate state
           │             ▲
           │             │ 780 nm (Probe laser)
           │             │
     5S₁/₂ ├─────────────●──────────  Ground state
           │
           └──────────────────────────►
```

**EIT Transmission Spectrum:**

```
    Probe Transmission
           ▲
      1.0  │                    ┌───────┐
           │                   /         \
           │                  /           \
           │                 /             \
      0.5  │                /               \
           │               /                 \
           │              /                   \
           │    ─────────/                     \─────────
      0.0  │
           └─────────────┬────────────────────────────►
                         │                    Probe Detuning
                    Δp = 0
                 (EIT Window)
                 
    With RF field: The EIT window SPLITS (Autler-Townes)
    
           ▲
      1.0  │                 ┌──┐     ┌──┐
           │                /    \   /    \
           │               /      \ /      \
           │              /        X        \
      0.5  │             /        / \        \
           │            /        /   \        \
           │    ───────/        /     \        \───────
      0.0  │
           └──────────────────┬───────────────────────►
                         Splitting ∝ |E_RF|
                         (Measured quantity)
```

**Osjetljivost vs frekvencija:**

| n (Principal) | RF Frequency | Sensitivity | Bandwidth |
|---------------|--------------|-------------|-----------|
| 50 | 50 GHz | ~100 nV/m/√Hz | 10 MHz |
| 55 | 17 GHz | ~200 nV/m/√Hz | 8 MHz |
| 60 | 6 GHz | ~300 nV/m/√Hz | 6 MHz |
| **70** | **500 MHz** | **~500 nV/m/√Hz** | **20-60 MHz** |
| 75 | 150 MHz | ~700 nV/m/√Hz | 30 MHz |

**QEDMMA koristi n≈70-75 za VHF band (100-200 MHz).**

